[ProMED thanks Prof Bercovier for transmitting this very interesting and timely large-scale study of the situation in Brazil, together with the following comments: "A very different picture of what is seen in Europe. Very few asymptomatic, the poor are always the highest victims, the tropical regions are more affected than the colder south and the children 0-4 are with the highest prevalence of antibodies and consequently the most infected. Their conclusion: the number of real Covid-19 cases is 6 times higher than the number of diagnosed cases." Please see the original URL PDF for very clear color-coded graphical data. -Mod.LXL]


